126int
127nvkm_object_fini(struct nvkm_object *object, bool suspend)
128{
129 const char *action = suspend ? "suspend" : "fini";
130 struct nvkm_object *child;
131 s64 time;
132 int ret;
133
134 nvif_debug(object, "%s children...\n", action);
135 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get());
136 list_for_each_entry(child, &object->tree, head) {
137 ret = nvkm_object_fini(child, suspend);
138 if (ret && suspend)
139 goto fail_child;
140 }
141
142 nvif_debug(object, "%s running...\n", action);
143 if (object->func->fini) {
144 ret = object->func->fini(object, suspend);
145 if (ret) {
146 nvif_error(object, "%s failed with %d\n", action, ret);
147 if (suspend)
148 goto fail;
149 }
150 }
151
152 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get()) - time;
153 nvif_debug(object, "%s completed in %"PRId64"us\n", action, time);
154 return 0;
155
156fail:
157 if (object->func->init) {
158 int rret = object->func->init(object);
159 if (rret)
160 nvif_fatal(object, "failed to restart, %d\n", rret);
161 }
162fail_child:
163 list_for_each_entry_continue_reverse(child, &object->tree, head) {
164 nvkm_object_init(child);
165 }
166 return ret;
167}
168
169int
170nvkm_object_init(struct nvkm_object *object)
171{
172 struct nvkm_object *child;
173 s64 time;
174 int ret;
175
176 nvif_debug(object, "init running...\n");
177 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get());
178 if (object->func->init) {
179 ret = object->func->init(object);
180 if (ret)
181 goto fail;
182 }
183
184 nvif_debug(object, "init children...\n");
185 list_for_each_entry(child, &object->tree, head) {
186 ret = nvkm_object_init(child);
187 if (ret)
188 goto fail_child;
189 }
190
191 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get()) - time;
192 nvif_debug(object, "init completed in %"PRId64"us\n", time);
193 return 0;
194
195fail_child:
196 list_for_each_entry_continue_reverse(child, &object->tree, head)
197 nvkm_object_fini(child, false);
198fail:
199 nvif_error(object, "init failed with %d\n", ret);
200 if (object->func->fini)
201 object->func->fini(object, false);
202 return ret;
203}
204
205void *
206nvkm_object_dtor(struct nvkm_object *object)
207{
208 struct nvkm_object *child, *ctemp;
209 void *data = object;
210 s64 time;
211
212 nvif_debug(object, "destroy children...\n");
213 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get());
214 list_for_each_entry_safe(child, ctemp, &object->tree, head) {
215 nvkm_object_del(&child);
216 }
217
218 nvif_debug(object, "destroy running...\n");
219 if (object->func->dtor)
220 data = object->func->dtor(object);
221 nvkm_engine_unref(&object->engine);
222 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get()) - time;
223 nvif_debug(object, "destroy completed in %"PRId64"us...\n", time);
224 return data;
225}
226
227void
228nvkm_object_del(struct nvkm_object **pobject)
229{
230 struct nvkm_object *object = *pobject;
231 if (object && !WARN_ON(!object->func)) {
232 *pobject = nvkm_object_dtor(object);
233 nvkm_client_remove(object->client, object);
234 list_del(&object->head);
235 kfree(*pobject);
236 *pobject = NULL;
237 }
238}
239
240void
241nvkm_object_ctor(const struct nvkm_object_func *func,
242 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, struct nvkm_object *object)
243{
244 object->func = func;
245 object->client = oclass->client;
246 object->engine = nvkm_engine_ref(oclass->engine);
247 object->oclass = oclass->base.oclass;
248 object->handle = oclass->handle;
249 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&object->head);
250 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&object->tree);
251#ifdef __NetBSD__
252 object->on_tree = false;
253#else
254 RB_CLEAR_NODE(&object->node);
255#endif
256 WARN_ON(oclass->engine && !object->engine);
257}
258
259int
260nvkm_object_new_(const struct nvkm_object_func *func,
261 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
262 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
263{
264 if (size == 0) {
265 if (!(*pobject = kzalloc(sizeof(**pobject), GFP_KERNEL)))
266 return -ENOMEM;
267 nvkm_object_ctor(func, oclass, *pobject);
268 return 0;
269 }
270 return -ENOSYS;
271}
272
273static const struct nvkm_object_func
274nvkm_object_func = {
275};
276
277int
278nvkm_object_new(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
279 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
280{
281 const struct nvkm_object_func *func =
282 oclass->base.func ? oclass->base.func : &nvkm_object_func;
283 return nvkm_object_new_(func, oclass, data, size, pobject);
284}
